[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Governance[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]1
[normal]2
[normal]. 
[normal]Cancer Research U
[normal]K
[normal] is a company limited by guarantee and is a registered charity.  It is governed by a Council of Trustees.  This Council is ultimately responsible for the Charity’s strategic direction, supported by a number of committees to which the Council delegates cert
[normal]ain authorities. 
[normal]These include 
[normal]a 
[normal]Nomination, Governance and Remuneration Committee
[normal], whose role is explained further below.
[normal] 
[normal]The Charity’s governance fully complies with the Code for the Voluntary and Community Sector, endorsed by the Charity Commission.
[normal] 
[normal] Co
[normal]uncil delegate
[normal]s
[normal] day-to-day running of the Charity 
[normal]to
[normal] the Executive Board, which is led by the Chief Executive
[normal]. 
[normal]The governance of 
[normal]Cancer Research UK 
[normal]is designed to match the
[normal] standards expected of a FTSE 250 company. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]13. 
[normal]Cancer Research UK’s 
[normal]T
[normal]rustees 
[normal]perform a
[normal]n essential
[normal] role in the effective governance of the Charity. 
[normal]Trustees do not receive payment for their services but 
[normal]are entitled to reclaim 
[normal]reasonable expenses for travel and subsistence incurred in attending meetings and events in 
[normal]an
[normal] official cap
[normal]acity.  
[normal]On average, e
[normal]ach 
[normal]T
[normal]rustee claimed
[normal] 
[normal]less than £1,900 
[normal]during
[normal] the year 2012/13.
